def: The gate of a mold, through which the melted metal is poured;runner, geat.
A firing in the direction of the length of a trench, or a lineof parapet or troops, etc.; a raking fire.
The act of announcing, or giving notice; that which announces;proclamation; publication.
Soft; tender; delicate. [Obs. or Prov. Eng.]
An iron or pope thimble or grommet worked into or attached tothe edges and corners of a sail; -- usually in the plural. Thecringles are used for making fast the bowline bridles, earings, etc.
Of a fistular form; tubular; pipe-shaped.Stalactite often occurs fistuliform. W. Philips.
The act of pouring off a clear liquor gently from its lees orsediment, or from one vessel into another.
The act or state of preponderating; preponderance; as, apreponderation of reasons. I. Watts.
Formed into a legion or legions; legionary. Shelley.
